<hl>
<seg id=1> Minister of Information Lamo: Demonstrators Participating in "Raging Fire Will Not Die" Should Not Become Puppets of Foreign Powers </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (Kuala Lumpur, Message), Malaysian Minister of Information Mohamed Lamo said that those involved in the "Raging Fire Will Not Die" demonstration should not become puppets of foreign powers and destroy the country. Instead, they should adopt more sensible approaches to expressing their desires. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> He said that compared to the use of violence and generation of chaos, it is more effective to express what one desires through sensible methods.  </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> According to a report by the Malaysian News Agency, after attending Ministry of Information Family Day activities yesterday, Mohamed Lamo told the media that the government has implemented measures to let people fully express their opinions, i.e., to let people express their comments and viewpoints through appropriate channels in the form of 500 "Opinion Expression Centers" set up throughout the nation.  </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> He said the government will study the opinions and heartfelt wishes expressed by the people and make improvement in order to meet the demands of the masses. </seg>
<seg id=6> He stressed that this is a practice of democratic nations. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> He also urged those who participated in the demonstration to deeply ponder the consequences of the demonstration. He added that the prosperity of today has been achieved only through the dedication and enthusiastic construction of Malaysia by people throughout the nation since its independence 41 years ago.  </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> He said that while demonstrators receive the support of foreign powers to further resist the government with all their strength, they do not realize that their conduct is a betrayal of national dignity. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> He indicated: "If foreigners want to come to Malaysia to invest, we extend an immense welcome. But if they pay demonstrators, we will certainly protest." </seg>
</p>
